-	Overview radar
-	Cubemaps
-	Optimized with nodraw for better FPS
-	Nav file for bots
-	Buy Zones
-	Custom textures by CGTextures at www.cgtextures.com
-	Custom skybox by Jaj

Gg_oldtimerscorner
============
The objective was to create a fast-paced gun game map, with high fps and is visually appealing.
============
Focused around a old street theme. One large building separates the map, and the combat zone is in a small market plaza. Smaller homes litter the outside. Smoke rises from the chimneys and birds chirp in the distance.
============
32slot, soundscape. Enjoy and provide serious and constructive feedback. Thanks to cheebs for Radar Overlay.
============

Ok so this is my second map for FPSBanana, and my first for my new studio Vertex Studio, which I'm glad to be a part of.

I did this all in one long ass night, full of restarts, this game is currently unavailable, and computer crashes, due to fucking ladders.

SO anyways, I'm really happy that I managed to release this within the 3 week limit lol, and my next project will be a realistic map, but I havent decided the actual map theme. Heres the summary of the map from my project page:

This is my first map for Vertex Studio!

After crashing my computer countless times and fixing a shit-ton of bugs, its here. Its a map in which you spawn in the same room as the enemy, only you're separated by a glass wall. You then jump down into the first fight pit, full of glass walls to fight through, then head to the corner and jump down to the crate-yard, overlooking the sea upon which your oil rig lies. Head up the ramp and climb the ladder to the top of this menacing dev textured beast and jump into the final fight pit, but be warned, the only way out of the pit is to die.

PLEASE enjoy the map because I put a lot of work into it :D

..::DISS4LIFE::.."

So there it is, I hope you enjoy this one better than my purple and black textured submission from earlier, but anyways, enjoy, and please rate, comment, and assess, that way I know what i did wrong, or maybe even right ;D

About :: GG_Office_Mini2
Hello World
This map is a remake of my old map ( gg_office_mini ) as the maps was decent attempt at mapping I decided to make a remake. More optimized, better game play, and what all the GG players want these days. I really focused on optimizing working with hint/skip textures for the first time. I learned a lot on optimazing and optimzed this map from 120fps to 200+ fps, Once you learn it's very easy.

The map has a basic style as the original map cs_office. This gg map is like a stipend version of it. Interms of gameplay i tested on a sample gg server with 24players and it was fun. Try it out your self.

Hope you like it.


-Cezaris LT

Hey Guys, this is my freshest Gun Game Map. Its the Location from a Office. The Map has 4 Main Corridors, and  the 2 bigger Corridors are the Spawnpoints for the Fractions. At the small Carridor on the Main Side i have put the Reception, with 2 little indoor Waterfalls (the Textures are in the Pack). And at the other small Corridor i have put the Toilettes with a broken Wall (you can go trough), and a Pipe System there pulls the Steam out. The Offices are in the Center from the Map. There is a Conference Room with some Couches and Tables in the Center too. You can see the costum PC Model and the Marijuhana Plant on my Screenes, the Stuff isnt in the Pack, you have the old Models. You can play the Map with 32 People.

I hope you like the Map, Have Fun

A map I created for Counter-Strike: Source, Gun-Game mod.

Still in alpha phase, and as such I have not really set my heart on any specific texture theme (just wanted to get off of the old dev textures.)

Also hasn't got any lighting scheme as of yet, I'm mostly trying to work out whether or not to change any of the layout or gameplay here.

Standard Nav included with the download, but the bots don't seem to like using the ladders. I figured this doesn't matter since most servers don't have bots. Buyzones included to prevent console errors. You can turn these off either using server cvars or by using the standard gungame settings.

Enjoi.

The Map:
==================
This map is plays in a small bunker underwater in the Ocean. Over this bunker
is a old city underwater.

How to play:
==================
You go to the vending machine and press E on the button, and there you get a weapon (ak47,m4a1,deagle,usp)

Then you wait for the doors ... 
Run outside of the spawning room and kill the others!

But when you stay in the spawning room you get killed after 7 seconds 
after the doors have been opened.

On the couches are knifes so if you have no ammo anymore you can do a
last man standing knife battle !

I hope you enjoy this map and have fun on our server ;)

So i was sick of studying the other day, and feeling inspired by the great cell shading tutorial by lost, combined with my love of trippy-glowing things, i decided i would make this map. Its a kind of new-ish take on the TRON theme, in that its more curved and has the trippy glowing thing going on. 
The layout makes for more close-up combat, with some oppurtunity for long range.

Hope you enjoy the map as much as i enjoyed making it.
